baseName.value: Reinforced concrete road safety barriers New Jersey profile: NJV50A600-ABESCA

generalComment.value:
The primary data collected in this study refers to production for the year 2022.


Based on M3


No cut-off elements were considered, therefore it is believed that the data represents at least 99% of the total flows (mass and energy) of phases A1, A2 and A3.

technologicalApplicability.value:
New Jersey profile road safety barriers are road safety devices designed and sized to resist to impacts from means of transport, dissipating the energy of the impact itself.
 "New Jersey type road safety barriers are manufactured goods essentially used in four configurations:
• CENTRAL SINGLE-ROW
• TWO-FIRED ASYMMETRIC
• SIDE EDGE
• BRIDGE EDGE
• TUNNEL EDGE
In the first two cases these are barriers placed in the center of the road to separate the two lanes and prevent vehicles access in the opposite direction. In the third and fourth cases the barrier is placed on both sides of the road or as an edge of a viaduct, in order to prevent vehicles from leaving the road. In the fifth and final case we are dealing with protective barriers to be installed inside the tunnels that allow the redirection of vehicles, minimizing the consequences of any collisions.
The types differ in section and may or may not be designed for anchoring to the road surface.
The modules are connected to each other at the top by rolled bars and sleeves, at the bottom by tie rods and plates."
